ublicProfile?language=EN>Kelyna Tempestwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#B76D00>(12/17/01 2:35:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fthelanyscoalitionofguildsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=147.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://fla.fg-a.com/usf261b3.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: PoA - we have the experience?</span><hr size=1> It looks like you and I are at the same stage in our epics, Sorych, hehe. I also need the sphere (multiples drop every time apparently), and to say hello to ol' Jaeil in the Hole, in order to complete swiftwind.<br>
<br>
However--and I cannot stress this enough--Air is very very very very (times 3 to the 9th power) nasty! I have only been there once, and it was a botched raid unfortunately. We had a big enough force, but we were wiped out on the second island without the baddies even breaking a sweat.<br>
<br>
An Air raid needs three things. 1) A leader with lots of previous experience, 2) Balanced groups of all 50+ (55+ is even better), and 3) people who will listen and *follow* instructions to the letter. Oh yeah, and someone with a big piggy bank. Air stones cost somewhere around 200pp each, and you need one for each group porting up. <br>
<br>
Worse, the only way between islands is to use the portal keys...levitate and CoH among other spells, do not work here. Neither do any kind of evacs, so the only way to leave is by jumping. This means, for every person you have over the limit of portal keys (I think 22 is the number? Can't remember) you need a coffin for *each* time they need to get to another island. It's also a good idea to buy a few extra, just in case. For all that, you *must* have a high level necro, so that you can use the stackable coffins...if not, prices just get ridiculous. I was the one who bought the coffins (stackable) for the Air raid I went on, and it ran me over 2k *ouch!*<br>
<br>
So naturally, you can only take so many with you, which makes the higher the level the better. You will also want someone with a list of everyone going, because as soon as a monster goes down, you need the right people looting the right pieces for the port keys...my reccommendation is to have that person just start going down the list calling names. That way, you know who has keys, and who will need to be summoned. Remember, the necro can only summon someone's corpse who is *in* his group.<br>
<br>
Have I scared you yet? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
To be honest, I do not know if we have the manpower and levels it would take to attempt Air. Wipeouts are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> horrible</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, especially on the pocketbook, and typically spell doom for the whole raid. That's why so few actually attempt the zone, and even then, its usually for epic pieces. I think your best bet is to hop on a raid with a guild that's done it a lot (DW is a good choice). There are usually more sphere's than there are rangers, so you'd have a good shot at picking one up. <p><center><img src="http://silverdragen.freeservers.com/images/sig21.jpg"> 
